<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Confirmed</strong>&nbsp;cases include&nbsp;<strong>presumptive positive</strong>&nbsp;cases.</p>

<p><strong>Death totals</strong> in the US include confirmed and probable, in accordance with <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/cases-updates/cases-in-us.html">CDC guidelines</a> as of April 14.</p>

<p><strong>Recovered cases </strong>outside China are estimates based on local media reports, and state and local reporting when available, and therefore may be substantially lower than the true number. &nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Active cases</strong>&nbsp;= total confirmed - total recovered - total deaths.</p>

<p><strong>Incidence Rate</strong>&nbsp;= confirmed cases per 100,000 persons.</p>

<p><strong>Case-Fatality Ratio</strong>&nbsp;(%) = Number recorded deaths / Number confirmed cases.</p>

<p><strong>US Testing Rate</strong>&nbsp;= total tested per 100,000 persons.</p>

<p><strong>US Hospitalization Rate (%)</strong>&nbsp;= Total number hospitalized / Number confirmed cases.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Point level</strong>: County level - US; Province/State level - China,&nbsp;Canada,&nbsp;Australia; Country level - other countries.&nbsp;All points (except for Australia)&nbsp;shown on the map are based on geographic centroids, and are not representative of a specific address, building or any location at a spatial scale finer than a province/state. Australian dots are located at the centroid of the largest city in each state.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Time Zones</strong>: lower-left corner indicator - your local time; lower-right corner plot - UTC.&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Note:&nbsp;All cases of COVID-19 in repatriated US citizens from the&nbsp;<strong>Diamond Princess</strong>&nbsp;are grouped together. These individuals have been assigned to various quarantine locations (in military bases and hospitals) around the US.&nbsp;This grouping is consistent with the CDC.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>*The names of locations included on the Website correspond with the official designations used by the U.S. Department of State.&nbsp;</p>
